Package com.jenmann.entity

Class Monster

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jenmann.entity.Monster
  • public class Monster
extends java.lang.Object
    The Monster class represents a singular monster from the DND 5e API. While the GetAllResponseItem currently only represents a monster, it represents the parsed-down version of the entity returned by the getAll method. In contrast, this entity represents the full monster. Some data provided by the API is purposefully left out of this entity for brevity, and because not all data was needed.
    Author:
    jcmann

               java.lang.String size,
               java.lang.String alignment,
               int armorClass,
               int hitPoints,
               java.lang.String hitDice)
        Constructs a Monster entity with all instance variables. This would be commonly used because the API should, hypothetically, return all this data.
        Parameters:
        index - lower snake case index
        name - monster name
        size - 5e-type size category
        alignment - chaotic/lawful good/evil
        armorClass - integer armor class
        hitPoints - maximum health points
        hitDice - monster's hit dice
